HEADWORD: Recantation
<hw>Re`can*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(r⟦emac⟧`k⟦acr⟧n*t⟦amac⟧"sh⟦ucr⟧n)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of recanting; a declaration that contradicts
a former one; that which is thus asserted in contradiction;
retraction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The poor man was imprisoned for this discovery, and forced to make
a public <qex>recantation</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Bp.
Stillingfleet.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recanter</ent>⟦br⟧
